      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Last season's Eureka winner BAY OF BISCAY (6) has had four weeks off since coming from this barrier for a fresh placing at this circuit and distance but there was plenty of merit in that effort, his first hitout for more than five months. Owns a good second up record so is likely to progress. FIGHTER COMMAND (5) has come from a similar draw to this in each of his three starts this time in, winning fresh and clocking in second in both attempts since. Owns an impressive record at this circuit and distance. Big chance. WAR DAN BUDDY (4) was a luckless second in the Riverina Championships last start where he raced wide but was looming strongly before copping a severe check. That added to a string of placings. Could break through. HES FROM HEAVEN NZ (3) draws well and two trial wins suggest he is back in good order so keep safe.",
